Detailed Description

A UserDispatcher can be added to any ExecutionContext as additional functional unit which can receive messages.
See also:
ExecutionContext::AddDispatcher()

Member Function Documentation

UserDispatcher* UserDispatcher::GetNext (   )  const [inline]
 

Returns the successor of the current user dispatcher.

void UserDispatcher::RegisterMessages (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

This method is invoked as soon as the user dispatcher is added to an execution context by ExecutionContext::AddDispatcher(). The derived user dispatcher should register all messages it wants to receive.

Reimplemented in BtAvrcpOperationService, BtAvrcpService, BtBppService, BtDevicePairRequest, BtDeviceSearchRequest, BtDeviceTrustRequest, BtDeviceUnpairRequest, BtDeviceUntrustRequest, BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest, BtRespondAuthorizationRequest, BtSddbService, BtSendPasskeyRequest, BtServiceVerifyRequest, BtSetRemoteDeviceNameRequest, BtDunService, BtFaxService, BtHfService, BtHsService, BtObexService, and MessageMapDispatcher.

void UserDispatcher::SetNext (  UserDispatcher *  next  )  [inline]
 

Sets the successor of the current user dispatcher. It should not be necessary for the MMI to invoke this method in a direct manner.

void UserDispatcher::UnregisterMessages (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

This method is invoked as soon as the user dispatcher is removed from an execution context by ExecutionContext::RemoveDispatcher(). The derived user dispatcher should unregister all messages it has registered inside UserDispatcher::RegisterMessages().

Reimplemented in BtAvrcpOperationService, BtAvrcpService, BtBppService, BtDevicePairRequest, BtDeviceSearchRequest, BtDeviceTrustRequest, BtDeviceUnpairRequest, BtDeviceUntrustRequest, BtQuerySupportedProfilesRequest, BtRespondAuthorizationRequest, BtSddbService, BtSendPasskeyRequest, BtServiceVerifyRequest, BtSetRemoteDeviceNameRequest, BtDunService, BtFaxService, BtHfService, BtHsService, BtObexService, and MessageMapDispatcher.
